           For problems 8.3 and 8.8: Use the 3rd bullet of Proposition 2.4.3 to create elements of desired order. 
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
           For problem 8.6: The {\it trivial} homomorphism <m>\varphi\colon G\to G'</m> is the homomorphism defined 
           by <m>\varphi(x)=1</m> for all <m>x\in G</m>. In other words, <m>\varphi</m> is trivial if and only if <m>\text{Im}(\varphi)=\{1\}</m>. 
          </p>
